<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-176] Exception prefixes should be human-readable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-176</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;OpenJPA prefixes all exception messages with a string of the form &quot;&amp;lt;exception type|is fatal|version&amp;gt;&quot;, restulting in strings like &quot;&amp;lt;4|false|0.9.6-incubating&amp;gt; org.apache.openjpa.persistence.PersistenceException&quot;. This isn&apos;t very useful to the casual observer, since no translation of the meaning of the fields is done.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it would be nice if we translated the fatal and type parameters, so that the string looked like &quot;&amp;lt;user-error|recoverable|0.9.6-incubating&amp;gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12365411">OPENJPA-176</key>
            <summary>Exception prefixes should be human-readable</summary>
