                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12483803" author="mprudhom" created="Sat, 24 Mar 2007 04:11:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch will change the prefix to look like, for example: &quot;&amp;lt;0.9.6-incubating fatal user error&amp;gt; org.apache.openjpa.persistence.PersistenceException&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any objections?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12483850" author="clr" created="Sat, 24 Mar 2007 15:54:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I like it. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What if the type is not one of the expected types? Perhaps we want to identify this case? Such as &quot;unexpected error&quot; or something.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12483852" author="mikedd" created="Sat, 24 Mar 2007 16:18:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like we just use type + &quot; error&quot; if the type isn&apos;t recognized. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 as it is, but I&apos;m not opposed to changing type + &quot; error&quot; to &quot;unexpected error&quot; or something similar. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12483867" author="mprudhom" created="Sat, 24 Mar 2007 19:38:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Implemented patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
